latestIgtvVideos.title: Night Skincare Regime  @cosmetofood_organics
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
As we know, our skin rests and naturally repairs itself at night, while we sleep. Thus a proper night care regime is required to improve your skin texture. Give your skin’s natural nighttime regime a boost with @cosmetofood and give your skin what it needs. 

Here’s the best order of the products to make sure you get the most out of them:

Facial cleanser: use @cosmetofood_organics Skinergy Mulberry & Licorice brightening face cleanser to clean your face. Massage the cleanser gently on your face and wash it off with lukewarm water. 

Exfoliate: Though it is not necessary to exfoliate your skin every day, if you find unwanted blackheads, you can follow it up using @cosmetofood_organics Skinergy Mulberry & Flaxseed brightening exfoliator. You can use it daily since the scrub particles are gentle and will not over-exfoliate. 

Moisturiser: Using a moisturiser is very important before you retire for the night. I personally love @cosmetofood_organics Skinergy Mulberry enriched brightening elixir. It removes dead skin cells and pollutants, soothes and rejuvenates the skin, nourishes the skin with vitamins and minerals and also maintains the pH balance of your skin. This leaves your skin fresh and perfectly prepped to absorb your skin regimen.

#skincare #skincareroutine #nightskincare #beauty #beautyblogger #cosmetofood_organic

Back at @dantamclinics after 20 days — and my Invisalign aligners are finally here! 🙌🏼✨

I’ve honestly been so excited for this moment. Starting this journey toward a straighter, more confident smile feels so real now. 😁🦷

I still remember my first visit like it was yesterday — that 3D scan totally blew my mind. It made everything feel so high-tech and personal.

And now, with my custom aligners in hand (flown in all the way from the US!), it’s finally go time.

The whole process has been such a breeze — super smooth, super professional, and honestly way easier than I expected.

Can’t wait to see how things shift in the next few weeks — and of course, I’ll be sharing every step with you. Let’s do this! 💫🫶
